cs.CV, cs.IR, cs.MM, cs.GR, cs.CL 

The paper proposes a method for segmenting nighttime sky/cloud images, which involves image processing and computer vision techniques. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also mentions the use of satellite communication, which suggests a possible connection to cs.IR (Information Retrieval). The use of superpixels and the release of a database may also indicate a connection to cs.MM (Multimedia). The study of atmospheric phenomena and weather analysis may suggest a connection to cs.GR (Graphics) or cs.CL (Computation and Language).
